<br>
Enjoy.<br>
<!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
Draft one. I loosely organized my notes and grouped 'em.<br>
<br>
~~~Debut~~~<br>
-New system will be on test soon and unveiled on live servers Dec 16.<br>
-The melee system will start with about 20 skills for each class with others to be added later.<br>
-The melee rebalance will be a free feature and not part of an expansion.<br>
<br>
~~~Skill Overview~~~<br>
-Not all effects will be only to increase dps. Debuffs and group enhancement were mentioned.<br>
-Openings should appear &quot;a few per fight,&quot; not constant button mashing.<br>
-Melee openings will be available to pure melee classes only.<br>
-Skills are instant like bash/kick/backstab and will not have cast times.<br>
-Skills are not dependant on position relative to the mob.<br>
<br>
~~~Gaining Skills~~~<br>
-New melee abilities will be gained via turning in the tome for that ability to a guildmaster.<br>
-Tomes for &lt;60 abilities wil be found on merchants, with some tomes being drop-only or quested.<br>
-The majority of 60+ ability tomes will be gained via a system very similiar to the current PoP parchment turnin method. <br>
<br>
~~~Openings~~~<br>
-Several openings will be linked to parry/block/dodge/riposte.<br>
-Other openings will be linked to regular and special attacks, so tanking is not necessary to use skills.<br>
-Haste/dual weild will only provide minimal increase to the frequency of openings. They are scaled around delay. (Kyur note: I assume how procrate is tuned currently, with haste decreasing rate/swing but maintaining frequency/time)<br>
-NPCs will now have a chance to &quot;fumble,&quot; creating an opening for anyone fighting it.<br>
-&quot;There will be a few opening types and several abilities possible for each opening&quot;<br>
<br>
~~~Aggro and Taunt~~~<br>
-Some skills will be used to directly influence aggro, whether it be lowering or gaining.<br>
-All melee with a taunt button will receive a message to notify them if taunt was successful.<br>
-Warriors will be given skills to gain and keep aggro, including one skill that will not require an opening.<br>
-Taunt itself will not be retuned.<br>
<br>
~~~Endurance Pool~~~<br>
-Endurance pool will be based on &quot;melee stats&quot; and regen is based on level.<br>
-Endurance boni will be added to existing gear.<br>
-Invigor type spells are being removed completely.<br>
-Jumping will take a minor amount of endurance.<br>
(Kyur note: Several asked, but no mention was made of actually removing the stamina bar. This seems like a safe assumption though.)<br>
-Existing disciplines will be retuned, added to the endurance system, and given their own timers. You will not be able to run more than one discipline at once.<br>
<br>
~~~UI Additions~~~<br>
-Openings will appear via a &quot;UI indicator&quot; with a button to click to activate the new abilities.<br>
-A new UI window will be added with hotbuttons for each skill. New keyboard shortcuts will be used to access these buttons.<br>
<br>
~~~Other Balance Information~~~<br>
-Other melee tweaks include increased warrior mitigation and monks being able to dodge attacks from behind.<br>
<br>
It was also mentioned that the new skill system was part of a full melee overhaul, but details were not mentioned. <br>
Also, One thing that stick out in my memory on warrior/knight balance was giving each &quot;equal desirability in different situations&quot; - whatever the hell that means.<br>
<br>
~Kyur<br>
